Is it easy to extend statistic job to collect informations from other type table?

I'm a begginer of doris. But i dug into this issue a bit. I think maybe this problem was caused by this https://github.com/apache/incubator-doris/pull/7371/files 
After this, call of LoadJob.beginTxn was moved from LoadJob.unprotectedExecute to SparkLoadPendingTask.executeTask, which was after the call of SparkLoadPendingTask.createEtlJobConf  and so in createEtlJobConf the transactionId was 0.

When A ColumnDict needs to be  converted to a normal Column, we need create a ```New Column```.
The ```New Column``` needs to reserve memory.
The ```New Column``` 's reserve size needs to keep same with ColumnDict's initial reserve size, instead of current ColumnDict's size.
Otherwise, subsequent writes to the ```New Column``` will access the unallocated memory area

runtime filter remove | q8 | q9 | q10 | q11 | q17 | q18 | q21 -- | -- | -- | -- | -- | -- | -- | -- OFF | 6.76s | 63.27s | 2.27s | 0.39s | 3.36s | 2.4s | 5.27s ON | 6.75s | 61.12s | 2.25s | 0.33s | 3.02s | 2.1s | 4.72s
